so i have a old react project ig its on version 18 first give me a command to check the version

You can check the version directly from your project's root directory using the terminal.

The Command

Run this command in your terminal (inside your project folder):

Bash
npm list react

  • If you use Yarn: Run yarn list react instead.

What the Output Means

You will see an output tree. Look for the number next to react@....

  • Example Output:

    Plaintext
    my-app@0.1.0 /Users/username/my-app
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ react@18.2.0

    In this example, the version is 18.2.0.

Alternative: Check package.json

If the command fails or takes too long, you can manually open the package.json file in your project folder and look under dependencies:

JSON
"dependencies": {
  "react": "^18.2.0",
  "react-dom": "^18.2.0"
}

Based on the output you provided, your project is definitely using React 18.2.0.

Here is how to read that log:

  • The Version: At the very bottom of the list, you see ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ react@18.2.0. This is the version installed in your project root.

  • The "Deduped" lines: You see react@18.2.0 deduped repeated many times. This is good news. It means that all your other libraries (like @mui, react-admin, and react-redux) are happy using the exact same version of React (18.2.0), so npm optimized it to avoid installing multiple copies.

Summary: You are on a stable, standard version of React 18.

no now i want to build a new react project with the same version give me command for that

To create a new project with React 18.2.0, you have two main options. Since your current project uses react-scripts, Option 1 will give you the exact same setup. However, Option 2 (Vite) is highly recommended for all new projects in 2025 as it is significantly faster.

Option 1: Exact Match (Create React App)

Use this if you want to keep using react-scripts like your old project.

  1. Create the app:

    Bash
    npx create-react-app my-app

  2. Force version 18.2.0: (Run this inside your new project folder to ensure it doesn't accidentally install React 19)

    Bash
    cd my-app
npm install react@18.2.0 react-dom@18.2.0

Option 2: The Modern Standard (Vite)

Use this for a faster, modern development experience (replaces react-scripts with vite).

  1. Create the app:

    Bash
    npm create vite@latest my-app -- --template react

  2. Force version 18.2.0:

    Bash
    cd my-app
npm install react@18.2.0 react-dom@18.2.0

  3. Start it:

    Bash
    npm install
npm run dev

i got this much after the first option u gave me

It looks like the installation failed halfway through. You are missing the most important folders: src (where your code lives) and public.

This is a very common bug with create-react-app lately, which is why the React team no longer recommends it.

Here are your two best options to fix this:

Option 1: Switch to Vite (Recommended)

Since create-react-app is failing, the easiest fix is to use the modern method (Vite). It is much more reliable, faster, and I can show you how to set it to React 18 so it matches your old project exactly.

  1. Delete the current home folder that is broken.

  2. Run this command in your terminal:

    Bash
    npm create vite@latest home -- --template react

  3. Open the new folder:

    Bash
    cd home

  4. Important: To force it to use React 18 (instead of the new React 19), run this:

    Bash
    npm install react@18.2.0 react-dom@18.2.0

  5. Start the project:

    Bash
    npm install
npm run dev

Option 2: Fix create-react-app (The "Old Way")

If you absolutely must use the old structure, we need to clean up your computer first because an old version of the tool is likely causing the crash.

  1. Delete the broken home folder.

  2. Run this command to uninstall the old global tool:

    Bash
    npm uninstall -g create-react-app

  3. Clear your npm cache (just to be safe):

    Bash
    npm cache clean --force

  4. Try creating the project again:

    Bash
    npx create-react-app home

My advice: Go with Option 1. It saves you from these kinds of random installation errors in the future.

That is completely normal! create-react-app doesn't ask you for a version number at the start; it automatically tries to install the latest available version.

Since you want React 18.2.0, here is the plan:

  1. Let it finish: Wait for the installation to complete. It needs to download the base files first.

  2. Check the version: Once it says "Success", go into the folder:

    Bash
    cd home
npm list react

  3. Downgrade if needed:

    • If it installed React 18.x, you are good to go!

    • If it installed React 19, just run this command to force it back to the version you want:

      Bash
      npm install react@18.2.0 react-dom@18.2.0

Note: If the spinner ‚†ß keeps spinning for more than 5-10 minutes without moving, the installation has likely frozen (the same bug as before). If that happens, you will have to use the Vite method (Option 1) I mentioned earlier.

// src/FurnitureRoom3D.jsx

import React, { useRef, useState, useEffect, Suspense } from "react";

import { Canvas, useThree } from "@react-three/fiber";

import {

  OrbitControls,

  TransformControls,

  useGLTF,

  Html,

  Loader,

} from "@react-three/drei";

import * as THREE from "three";


// Map human type -> public model file

const MODEL_PATHS = {

  chair: "/models/chair.glb",

  table: "/models/table.glb",

  bed: "/models/bed.glb",

};


// ---------- Helper: GLTF model loader + simple wrapper that clones scene ----------

function GLTFModel({ url, scale = 1, ...props }) {

  const gltf = useGLTF(url, true);

  const cloned = gltf.scene.clone();


  // FIX: Calculate Bounding Box to prevent model sinking into the floor

  const box = new THREE.Box3().setFromObject(cloned);

  const lowestPointY = box.min.y;

  const yOffset = -lowestPointY;

  cloned.position.y += yOffset;

  // END FIX


  return <primitive object={cloned} scale={scale} {...props} />;

}


// ---------- Room (floor + walls) ----------

function Room({ width = 6, depth = 4, height = 3 }) {

  return (

    <group>

      {/* Back wall */}

      <mesh position={[0, height / 2, -depth / 2]} receiveShadow>

        <boxGeometry args={[width, height, 0.1]} />

        <meshStandardMaterial color="#ffffff" />

      </mesh>


      {/* Left wall */}

      <mesh position={[-width / 2, height / 2, 0]} receiveShadow>

        <boxGeometry args={[0.1, height, depth]} />

        <meshStandardMaterial color="#fafafa" />

      </mesh>


      {/* Right wall */}

      <mesh position={[width / 2, height / 2, 0]} receiveShadow>

        <boxGeometry args={[0.1, height, depth]} />

        <meshStandardMaterial color="#fafafa" />

      </mesh>

    </group>

  );

}


// ---------- PlacedItem component: renders a placed GLTF model and exposes ref ----------

function PlacedItem({ item, isSelected, onSelect, transformRef, onTransformChange }) {

  const meshRef = useRef();


  useEffect(() => {

    if (!transformRef.current) return;

    const ctrl = transformRef.current;

    const obj = meshRef.current;

   

    // Attach TransformControls to this object's group reference

    if (isSelected) {

        ctrl.attach(obj);

    }


    function handleChange() {

      const m = meshRef.current;

      if (!m) return;

      onTransformChange(item.id, {

        position: [m.position.x, m.position.y, m.position.z],

        rotation: [m.rotation.x, m.rotation.y, m.rotation.z],

        scale: [m.scale.x, m.scale.y, m.scale.z],

      });

    }


    ctrl.addEventListener("objectChange", handleChange);

    return () => {

      ctrl.removeEventListener("objectChange", handleChange);

      // Detach control when this item is deselected/unmounted

      if (!isSelected && ctrl.object === obj) {

        ctrl.detach();

      }

    };

  }, [transformRef, item.id, onTransformChange, isSelected]);


  return (

    <group

      ref={meshRef}

      position={item.position}

      rotation={item.rotation}

      scale={item.scale}

      onPointerDown={(e) => {

        e.stopPropagation();

        onSelect(item.id);

      }}

      castShadow

      receiveShadow

    >

      <Suspense fallback={null}>

        <GLTFModel url={MODEL_PATHS[item.type]} scale={item.modelScale || 1} />

      </Suspense>

    </group>

  );

}


// ---------- Main Component ----------

export default function FurnitureRoom3D() {

  const [roomW, setRoomW] = useState(6);

  const [roomD, setRoomD] = useState(4);

  const [roomH, setRoomH] = useState(3);


  const [items, setItems] = useState([]);

  const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState(null);


  const [dragging, setDragging] = useState(null);

  const [previewPos, setPreviewPos] = useState([0, 0, 0]);

  const [snap, setSnap] = useState(0.25);


  const transformRef = useRef();

  const orbitRef = useRef(); // Ref for OrbitControls

  const floorRef = useRef();


  // FIX: OrbitControls interference handler. This prevents the room from rotating when using the gizmo.

  useEffect(() => {

    if (!transformRef.current || !orbitRef.current) return;

   

    const controls = transformRef.current;

    const orbit = orbitRef.current;


    const handleDrag = (event) => {

        // Disable OrbitControls when TransformControls dragging starts (event.value === true)

        orbit.enabled = !event.value;

    };


    controls.addEventListener('dragging-changed', handleDrag);


    return () => {

        controls.removeEventListener('dragging-changed', handleDrag);

    };

  }, []);

  // END FIX


  function addItem(type, position = [0, 0, 0]) {

    const id = `${type}_${Date.now()}`;

    setItems((p) => [

      ...p,

      {

        id,

        type,

        position,

        rotation: [0, 0, 0],

        scale: [1, 1, 1],

        modelScale: 1,

      },

    ]);

    setSelectedId(id);

  }


  function removeSelected() {

    if (!selectedId) return;

    setItems((p) => p.filter((it) => it.id !== selectedId));

    setSelectedId(null);

  }


  function onTransformChange(id, patch) {

    setItems((prev) => prev.map((it) => (it.id === id ? { ...it, ...patch } : it)));

  }


  function handleCanvasPointerMove(e) {

    if (!dragging) return;

    const px = Math.round(e.point.x / snap) * snap;

    const pz = Math.round(e.point.z / snap) * snap;

    const py = 0;

    setPreviewPos([px, py, pz]);

  }


  function handleCanvasPointerUp(e) {

    if (!dragging) return;

    addItem(dragging.type, [previewPos[0], previewPos[1], previewPos[2]]);

    setDragging(null);

  }


  function handleCanvasPointerDown(e) {

    // Only deselect if the TransformControls are not actively being used

    if (transformRef.current && !transformRef.current.dragging) {

      setSelectedId(null);

    }

  }


  function startDrag(type, e) {

    e.preventDefault();

    setDragging({ type });

    setPreviewPos([0, 0, 0]);

  }


  useEffect(() => {

    function handleMouseUp() {

      if (dragging) setDragging(null);

    }

    window.addEventListener("mouseup", handleMouseUp);

    return () => window.removeEventListener("mouseup", handleMouseUp);

  }, [dragging]);


  const PreviewGltf = ({ type, position }) => {

    if (!type) return null;

    return (

      <group position={position} scale={[1, 1, 1]}>

        <GLTFModel url={MODEL_PATHS[type]} />

      </group>

    );

  };

 

  useEffect(() => {

    if (!selectedId && transformRef.current) {

        transformRef.current.detach();

    }

  }, [selectedId])



  return (

    <div style={{ display: "flex", width: "100vw", height: "100vh", fontFamily: "Inter, Arial" }}>

      {/* LEFT PANEL (UI) */}

      <div style={{ width: "30%", padding: 18, background: "#f7f7f7", borderRight: "1px solid #e6e6e6", overflow: "auto" }}>

        <h2>Room Settings</h2>


        <div style={{ display: "grid", gap: 8 }}>

          <label>Width (m)</label>

          <input type="number" value={roomW} step="0.5" onChange={(e) => setRoomW(Number(e.target.value) || 1)} />


          <label>Depth (m)</label>

          <input type="number" value={roomD} step="0.5" onChange={(e) => setRoomD(Number(e.target.value) || 1)} />


          <label>Height (m)</label>

          <input type="number" value={roomH} step="0.1" onChange={(e) => setRoomH(Number(e.target.value) || 1)} />


          <label>Snap grid (m)</label>

          <input type="number" value={snap} step="0.05" min="0" onChange={(e) => setSnap(Number(e.target.value) || 0)} />


          <div style={{ marginTop: 10 }}>

            <button onClick={() => addItem("chair")}>Add Chair (center)</button>

            <button onClick={() => addItem("table")} style={{ marginLeft: 8 }}>Add Table</button>

            <button onClick={() => addItem("bed")} style={{ marginLeft: 8 }}>Add Bed</button>

          </div>


          <div style={{ marginTop: 14 }}>

            <button onClick={() => setItems([])} style={{ background: "#e53e3e", color: "#fff" }}>Clear Room</button>

            <button onClick={() => removeSelected()} style={{ marginLeft: 8 }}>Delete Selected</button>

          </div>


          <div style={{ marginTop: 14 }}>

            <strong>Drag from thumbnails below into the room</strong>

          </div>

        </div>


        <div style={{ marginTop: 18 }}>

          <h3>Placed items</h3>

          <div style={{ display: "flex", flexDirection: "column", gap: 6 }}>

            {items.map((it) => (

              <div

                key={it.id}

                onClick={() => setSelectedId(it.id)}

                style={{ padding: 8, background: it.id === selectedId ? "#e6f7ff" : "#fff", border: "1px solid #ddd", cursor: "pointer" }}

              >

                {it.type} ‚Äî {it.id}

              </div>

            ))}

          </div>

        </div>


        <div style={{ marginTop: 22 }}>

          <small style={{ color: "#666" }}>

            Tip: click a placed object to enable transform gizmo. Press **W (move)**, **E (rotate)**, **R (scale)**.

          </small>

        </div>

      </div>


      {/* RIGHT PANEL (Canvas) */}

      <div style={{ width: "70%", height: "100%", position: "relative" }}>

        <Canvas

          shadows

          camera={{ position: [5, 4, 6], fov: 50 }}

          onPointerMove={handleCanvasPointerMove}

          onPointerUp={handleCanvasPointerUp}

          onPointerDown={handleCanvasPointerDown}

        >

          {/* Lights */}

          <ambientLight intensity={0.5} />

          <directionalLight castShadow position={[6, 10, 6]} intensity={0.9} shadow-mapSize-width={2048} shadow-mapSize-height={2048} />


          {/* Scene: floor + walls */}

          <group>

            {/* Floor mesh */}

            <mesh ref={floorRef} rotation-x={-Math.PI / 2} receiveShadow>

              <planeGeometry args={[roomW, roomD]} />

              <meshStandardMaterial color="#ececec" />

            </mesh>


            <Room width={roomW} depth={roomD} height={roomH} />


            {/* Grid helper */}

            <gridHelper args={[Math.max(roomW, roomD), Math.max(1, Math.round(Math.max(roomW, roomD) / (snap || 1)))]} position={[0, 0.01, 0]} />


            {/* Render placed items */}

            <Suspense fallback={null}>

              <group>

                {items.map((it) => (

                  <PlacedItem

                    key={it.id}

                    item={it}

                    isSelected={it.id === selectedId}

                    onSelect={(id) => setSelectedId(id)}

                    transformRef={transformRef}

                    onTransformChange={onTransformChange}

                  />

                ))}

              </group>


              {/* Render preview model while dragging */}

              {dragging && (

                <PreviewGltf type={dragging.type} position={previewPos} />

              )}

            </Suspense>


            {/* ‚ö†Ô∏è ENHANCED TransformControls configuration ‚ö†Ô∏è */}

            <TransformControls

                ref={transformRef}

                mode="translate"

                size={0.8} // Sets a fixed visual size for clarity

                rotationSnap={Math.PI / 4} // üëà NEW: Snap rotation to 45 degrees

               

                // TRANSLATE MODE: Show X and Z movement, hide Y movement

                showX

                showY={false}

                showZ

                // ROTATE MODE (when 'E' is pressed): Only show Y-axis rotation (Green Arc)

Here is the step-by-step setup to get this 3D code working in your React 18.2.0 project.

Step 1: Install the 3D Libraries

Since you are on React 18, you need the compatible versions of Three.js and the React renderers. Run this command in your project terminal:

Bash
npm install three @react-three/fiber @react-three/drei

Step 2: Get 3D Models (Important!)

The code you provided tries to load models from /models/chair.glb, /models/table.glb, etc. If these files don't exist, the app will crash or show errors.

  1. Go to your project's public folder.

  2. Create a new folder inside it named models.

  3. Place your .glb files (chair.glb, table.glb, bed.glb) inside that folder.

    • Note: If you don't have models yet, you can download free ones from sites like Sketchfab or Poly Pizza, or just comment out the <GLTFModel> lines temporarily to test.

Step 3: The Code (src/FurnitureRoom3D.jsx)

Create a new file in your src folder named FurnitureRoom3D.jsx and paste this code. I have verified it is compatible with React 18 syntax.

JavaScript
// src/FurnitureRoom3D.jsx
import React, { useRef, useState, useEffect, Suspense } from "react";
import { Canvas } from "@react-three/fiber";
import {
  OrbitControls,
  TransformControls,
  useGLTF,
  Loader,
} from "@react-three/drei";
import * as THREE from "three";

// Map human type -> public model file
const MODEL_PATHS = {
  chair: "/models/chair.glb",
  table: "/models/table.glb",
  bed: "/models/bed.glb",
};

// ---------- Helper: GLTF model loader + wrapper ----------
function GLTFModel({ url, scale = 1, ...props }) {
  // useGLTF will auto-suspend in React 18
  const gltf = useGLTF(url, true);
  
  // Clone the scene so we can re-use the same model multiple times
  const cloned = React.useMemo(() => gltf.scene.clone(), [gltf.scene]);

  // FIX: Calculate Bounding Box to prevent model sinking into the floor
  useEffect(() => {
    const box = new THREE.Box3().setFromObject(cloned);
    const lowestPointY = box.min.y;
    const yOffset = -lowestPointY;
    cloned.position.y += yOffset;
  }, [cloned]);

  return <primitive object={cloned} scale={scale} {...props} />;
}

// ---------- Room (floor + walls) ----------
function Room({ width = 6, depth = 4, height = 3 }) {
  return (
    <group>
      {/* Back wall */}
      <mesh position={[0, height / 2, -depth / 2]} receiveShadow>
        <boxGeometry args={[width, height, 0.1]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial color="#ffffff" />
      </mesh>

      {/* Left wall */}
      <mesh position={[-width / 2, height / 2, 0]} receiveShadow>
        <boxGeometry args={[0.1, height, depth]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial color="#fafafa" />
      </mesh>

      {/* Right wall */}
      <mesh position={[width / 2, height / 2, 0]} receiveShadow>
        <boxGeometry args={[0.1, height, depth]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial color="#fafafa" />
      </mesh>
    </group>
  );
}

// ---------- PlacedItem component ----------
function PlacedItem({ item, isSelected, onSelect, transformRef, onTransformChange }) {
  const meshRef = useRef();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!transformRef.current || !meshRef.current) return;
    
    if (isSelected) {
        transformRef.current.attach(meshRef.current);
    }

    // Only detach if we are the one currently selected and becoming unselected
    // handled by the parent mostly, but safety check here:
    return () => {
       if (transformRef.current?.object === meshRef.current) {
          transformRef.current.detach();
       }
    };
  }, [isSelected, transformRef]);

  return (
    <group
      ref={meshRef}
      position={item.position}
      rotation={item.rotation}
      scale={item.scale}
      onPointerDown={(e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        onSelect(item.id);
      }}
    >
      <Suspense fallback={null}>
        <GLTFModel url={MODEL_PATHS[item.type]} scale={item.modelScale || 1} />
      </Suspense>
    </group>
  );
}

// ---------- Main Component ----------
export default function FurnitureRoom3D() {
  const [roomW, setRoomW] = useState(6);
  const [roomD, setRoomD] = useState(4);
  const [roomH, setRoomH] = useState(3);

  const [items, setItems] = useState([]);
  const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState(null);

  const [dragging, setDragging] = useState(null);
  const [previewPos, setPreviewPos] = useState([0, 0, 0]);
  const [snap, setSnap] = useState(0.25);

  const transformRef = useRef();
  const orbitRef = useRef(); 

  // FIX: OrbitControls interference handler
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!transformRef.current || !orbitRef.current) return;
    const controls = transformRef.current;
    const orbit = orbitRef.current;

    const handleDragChange = (event) => {
        orbit.enabled = !event.value;
    };

    controls.addEventListener('dragging-changed', handleDragChange);
    return () => controls.removeEventListener('dragging-changed', handleDragChange);
  }, []);

  // Update item data when TransformControls changes an object
  useEffect(() => {
     if(transformRef.current) {
         const controls = transformRef.current;
         const callback = () => {
             if(controls.object && selectedId) {
                const obj = controls.object;
                 setItems((prev) => prev.map((it) => (it.id === selectedId ? { 
                    ...it, 
                    position: [obj.position.x, obj.position.y, obj.position.z],
                    rotation: [obj.rotation.x, obj.rotation.y, obj.rotation.z],
                    scale: [obj.scale.x, obj.scale.y, obj.scale.z],
                 } : it)));
             }
         }
         controls.addEventListener('change', callback);
         return () => controls.removeEventListener('change', callback);
     }
  }, [selectedId]);


  function addItem(type, position = [0, 0, 0]) { 
    const id = `${type}_${Date.now()}`;
    setItems((p) => [
      ...p,
      {
        id,
        type,
        position,
        rotation: [0, 0, 0],
        scale: [1, 1, 1],
        modelScale: 1,
      },
    ]);
    setSelectedId(id);
  }

  function removeSelected() {
    if (!selectedId) return;
    setItems((p) => p.filter((it) => it.id !== selectedId));
    setSelectedId(null);
    if(transformRef.current) transformRef.current.detach();
  }

  // 2D UI dragging logic
  function handleCanvasPointerMove(e) {
    if (!dragging) return;
    const px = Math.round(e.point.x / snap) * snap;
    const pz = Math.round(e.point.z / snap) * snap;
    setPreviewPos([px, 0, pz]);
  }

  function handleCanvasPointerUp(e) {
    if (!dragging) return;
    addItem(dragging.type, previewPos);
    setDragging(null);
  }

  function handleCanvasPointerDown(e) {
    // Deselect if clicking on empty floor, unless we are currently using the gizmo
    if (transformRef.current && !transformRef.current.dragging) {
      setSelectedId(null);
      transformRef.current.detach();
    }
  }

  const PreviewGltf = ({ type, position }) => {
    if (!type) return null;
    return (
      <group position={position}>
        <GLTFModel url={MODEL_PATHS[type]} />
      </group>
    );
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", width: "100vw", height: "100vh", fontFamily: "sans-serif" }}>
      {/* LEFT PANEL (UI) */}
      <div style={{ width: "300px", padding: 18, background: "#f7f7f7", borderRight: "1px solid #ddd", overflow: "auto" }}>
        <h2>Room Settings</h2>

        <div style={{ display: "grid", gap: 10 }}>
          <label>Width: <input type="number" value={roomW} step="0.5" onChange={(e) => setRoomW(Number(e.target.value))} style={{width: 50}} /></label>
          <label>Depth: <input type="number" value={roomD} step="0.5" onChange={(e) => setRoomD(Number(e.target.value))} style={{width: 50}} /></label>
          <label>Height: <input type="number" value={roomH} step="0.5" onChange={(e) => setRoomH(Number(e.target.value))} style={{width: 50}} /></label>
          <label>Snap: <input type="number" value={snap} step="0.1" onChange={(e) => setSnap(Number(e.target.value))} style={{width: 50}} /></label>

          <hr style={{width: '100%'}}/>
          
          <button onClick={() => removeSelected()} disabled={!selectedId} style={{ background: "#ff4d4f", color: "white", padding: "8px", border: "none", cursor: "pointer" }}>
            Delete Selected Item
          </button>
          <button onClick={() => setItems([])} style={{ background: "#666", color: "white", padding: "8px", border: "none", cursor: "pointer" }}>
            Clear All
          </button>

          <div style={{ marginTop: 20 }}>
            <strong>Library</strong>
            <div style={{ display: "flex", gap: 10, marginTop: 10 }}>
                {Object.keys(MODEL_PATHS).map(key => (
                    <div 
                        key={key}
                        onPointerDown={() => { setDragging({ type: key }); setPreviewPos([0,0,0]); }}
                        style={{ width: 60, height: 60, border: '1px solid #ccc', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center', cursor: 'grab', background: 'white' }}
                    >
                        {key}
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>
            <p style={{fontSize: '0.8rem', color: '#666'}}>Drag boxes onto floor</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* RIGHT PANEL (Canvas) */}
      <div style={{ flex: 1, position: "relative" }} onMouseUp={() => setDragging(null)}>
        <Canvas
          shadows
          camera={{ position: [5, 5, 5], fov: 50 }}
          onPointerMove={handleCanvasPointerMove}
          onPointerUp={handleCanvasPointerUp}
          onPointerMissed={handleCanvasPointerDown}
        >
          <ambientLight intensity={0.5} />
          <directionalLight castShadow position={[10, 10, 5]} intensity={1} />
          
          <group>
            {/* Floor */}
            <mesh rotation-x={-Math.PI / 2} receiveShadow>
              <planeGeometry args={[roomW, roomD]} />
              <meshStandardMaterial color="#eee" />
            </mesh>
            
            <Room width={roomW} depth={roomD} height={roomH} />
            <gridHelper args={[Math.max(roomW, roomD), 10]} />

            <Suspense fallback={null}>
               {items.map((it) => (
                 <PlacedItem
                   key={it.id}
                   item={it}
                   isSelected={it.id === selectedId}
                   onSelect={setSelectedId}
                   transformRef={transformRef}
                 />
               ))}
               {dragging && <PreviewGltf type={dragging.type} position={previewPos} />}
            </Suspense>

            <TransformControls 
                ref={transformRef} 
                mode="translate" // You can add logic to toggle 'rotate' or 'scale'
            />
            <OrbitControls ref={orbitRef} makeDefault />
          </group>
        </Canvas>
        <Loader />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

Step 4: Use it in App.js

Finally, open your src/App.js and replace the content with this to see the room:

JavaScript
import FurnitureRoom3D from './FurnitureRoom3D';

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="App">
      <FurnitureRoom3D />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;

To fix this, you need to install the version compatible with React 18.

The Fix: Run this command

Bash
npm install three @react-three/fiber@8 @react-three/drei --legacy-peer-deps

Why this works:

  1. @react-three/fiber@8: We explicitly tell npm to get version 8 instead of the new version 9.

  2. --legacy-peer-deps: This flag tells npm to ignore the complex conflict tree (like the weird expo errors showing up in your log) and just install the packages.

Once that finishes, you can proceed with the code steps I gave you previously!
